 Congratulations, you guys just helped make probably the most impressive game I've ever laid eyes on.<br>
<br>
- The graphics blow Dungeon Siege out of the water.  Animations are excellent, and the atmosphere is immersive.  You all are animators, right?  Top notch job.  Highest notch, in fact.<br>
<br>
- The character development system is incredible.  I'm a big fan of D&amp;D 3rd edition, so take this with a small grain of salt.  But for those not familiar with the system:<br>
<br>
You have standard race/class selection, just like EQ (7 races, 12 classes)<br>
<br>
You have complete control on ability distribution, with lots of hard choices to make.<br>
<br>
You get abotu 20 skills to raise.  Skill points are a limited commodity (except for maybe high intelligence wizards), so there are also lots of hard choices here.<br>
<br>
You get 20+ feats to choose from, many of which have multiple options.  You get one every 3rd level, maximum level is 20th, so unless you are playing a fighter (who gets LOTS of extra feats), these are some of your hardest choices.  I LOVE it!<br>
<br>
Just into the story right now.  I can't complain about it- the environment is so immersive that the story can be weak and it'll still work wonderfully.  Add to this that the editor tools are some of the best you've ever seen and you have near-infinite replayability.<br>
<br>
Total Kudos.  There are some bugs, apparently, but none that I've seen.  The game is making me think of re-cancelling my EQ account.<br>
<br>
By the way, if you have any bit of the designer's ear, how about item creation feats and prestige classes in the expansion? ;-)<br>
<br>
Puggins Fizzlefoot<br>
